Responsibilities
Responsibilities:
Maintain the training database To lead training activities Administer MIS like Training artefacts, TNA, TRF, Feedback, attendance etc., according to CMMi, ISMS standards Administer online E-Learning portals. Generate and publish E-learning reports weekly/ monthly to relevant stakeholders. Administer Training Intranet portal (gurucool) and ensure 100% compliance on updating the training material, IJP positions, R&R; photos, JDs. Prepare and publish monthly performance score cards. Coordinate for lab requirements to host external / internal training programs and smooth execution of training delivery. Co-ordinate with the facilities team for logistics like training halls, R & R certificates, Mementos etc., to ensure external training requirements are met. Maintain the library. Conduct process / product training to the floor according to the requirement. Vendor management HR:
Identify and source profiles from the job portals according to the skillset. Coordinate with Interview panel team to schedule the interview if required. Coordinate with the shortlisted candidates for the respective documents. Coordinate with internal HR team to initiate the offer process, new joiner formalities. Coordinate with KC team for any data or updates. Release new joiners, IJP & Buddy referral mailers across ITP. Publish quarterly communication calendar across KITP. Reports:
Publish monthly reports Consolidate and prepare HR & TD monthly review deck Responsible to prepare and publish Headcount, joiners, and leavers report across ITP. Review & update Org Chart on monthly basis. Publish Quarterly Attrition analysis report to the operations team. Publish attrition projection report on monthly basis. Release communication flyers about HR, TD activities to the floor. Skill Set: 3-4 Years of Experience training. Ability to take initiative. Intermediate knowledge on using MS Office tools like Ms-Excel, PowerPoint, Word etc. Excellent interpersonal and communication skills (Written and Verbal). Ability to clearly articulate situations / issues to cross-functional teams and client. People management skills. CMMi audit knowledge or any training certifications will be an added advantage. Skill Set: 3-4 Years of Experience training. Ability to take initiative. Intermediate knowledge on using MS Office tools like Ms-Excel, PowerPoint, Word etc. Excellent interpersonal and communication skills (Written and Verbal). Ability to clearly articulate situations / issues to cross-functional teams and client. People management skills.
